3.Text: WELL DATA CARD 	TOGA - FAIRVIEW 66 	PAGE 2 of 2
SUMMARY
Fairview 71 is a Bandanna coal seam gas development well located in PL 99 Queensland, on the
Fairview Field approximately 50 kilometres east of the township of Injune in central Queensland.
The nearest wells are Fairview 72 (2 kilometres east) and Fairview 62 (1.4 kilometres southeast)
drilled by TOGA and Tri-Star respectively. TOGA is the permit operator and Tri-Star is the current
permit holder.
The Fairview 71 was drilled with air and foam to a total depth of 688.0 m. Surface casing (36#
245 mm K55) was set at 254.57 m and cemented to surface to protect the Precipice Sandstone
aquifer. Intermediate casing (23# 178 mm K55) was set at 598.0 m to isolate the Triassic Rewan
section of the hole from the objective Permian Bandanna Formation. Two wireline log runs were
conducted; the first after topping the first Bandanna coal to evaluate Rewan sandstone potential
and the second at TD for the Bandanna coal section.
Fairview 71 intersected an abbreviated sequence of the Surat Basin comprised of the Evergreen
Formation and Precipice Sandstone followed by the Bowen Basin's Rewan Formation and TD'd in
the Permian Bandanna Formation. Stratigraphic control was good with the Bandanna formation
intersected 4 m low to prognosis. The primary target, the Bandanna Formation coals, intersected a
net 9.9 m of coal.
The Bandanna coal section was opened to approximately 222 mm (83/4") with an under-reamer to
666 m. After blowing the well dry, a bucket test was run with an approximate flow rate of 233.4 m
water/day (1468 bwpd). The well was flowed through the separator with a 0.375" orifice at 6 psi for
a 	rate of 2022 m3/day (71 Mcfd). The well was then cleaned out several times. The well
demonstrated a final flow rate of gas at 2888 m3/day (102 Mcfd) and water at 265.8 mi/day
(1672 bpd). A kill string of 89 mm 13.84 kg/m J55 EUE tubing was run in the well.
L. DeVattimo provided onsite drilling supervision for Tipperary Oil and Gas (Australia) Pty Limited.
The well location survey, drill time curve, and well completion schematic are include in Appendices
1 through 3.
